'''Khatun Sapnara''' (born April 1967) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[barrister]] and part time [[judge]].

==Early life==
Khatun Sapnara was born in [[Sylhet]], [[Bangladesh]] and came to the [[United Kingdom]] as a child. She is the daughter of late Mimbor Ali, who honoured by the Bangladeshi Government for his significant contribution to the [[Bangladesh Liberation War|liberation of Bangladesh]].

In 1988, Sapnara graduated with an [[Bachelor of Laws|LLB (Hons)]] from [[London School of Economics]] and [[Political Science]] at [[University of London]].<ref name="bbwhoswho08">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbwhoswho.co.uk/Profile/Sapnara,%20Ms%20Khatun.pdf|title=Ms. Khatun Sapnara|work=British Bangladeshi Who's Who 2008|location= |publisher=British Bangla Media Group|date=October 2008|page=190|accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref><ref name="bbwhoswho09">{{cite web |url=http://www.bbwhoswho.co.uk/whoswho_09.pdf|title=Khatun Sapnara|work=British Bangladeshi Who's Who 2009|location= |publisher=British Bangla Media Group|date=October 2009|page=117|accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref><ref name="history">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.history.org.uk/resources/general_news_250.html|title=Enforced marriage law forces couple apart|work= |location= |publisher=''The Historical Association''|date=19 March 2009|accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref>

==Career==
In 1990, she was called to the [[Bar (law)|Bar]].<ref name="history"/> She practises from Coram Barristers Chambers in [[London]] and specialises in [[Family law]].

In 2003, she was the first ethnic person to be elected to the Family Law Bar Association Committee. In 2004, Sapnara was appointed by the [[Lord Chancellor]] [[Charles Falconer, Baron Falconer of Thoroton|Baron Charles Falconer of Thoroton]] to the [[Family Justice Council]], which is a body of experts to advise the [[Government]] on all aspects of the family justice system<ref name="coramchambers">{{cite web |url=http://www.coramchambers.co.uk/barristers/profiles/khatun_sapnara|title=Khatun Sapnara|publisher=Coram Chambers|date= |accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref> She assisted in formulating and drafting the [[Forced Marriage (Civil Protection) Act 2007]].<ref name="bbc">{{cite news |last=Jones|first=Meirion|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/newsnight/8165684.stm|title=Enforced marriage law forces couple apart|work= |location= |publisher=''[[BBC News]]''|date=24 July 2009|accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref> In 2006, she was appointed as a [[Recorder (judge)|Recorder]] of the Crown, which made her the only [[British Bangladeshi|Bangladeshi]] in a senior judicial position.<ref name="bbwhoswho08"/><ref name="bbwhoswho09"/>

Sapnara has served as Director/Chair of a number of charities and voluntary sector organisations and lectures widely on issues relating to family law.<ref name="4brick">{{cite web |url=http://www.4brick.co.uk/Barristers/KS.htm|title=Khatun Sapnara|publisher= CORAM - Barristers|date= |accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Sapnara is married with two children.<ref name="bbwhoswho08"/><ref name="bbwhoswho09"/>

